## 9. BUILD ORDER (Follow This Sequence)

Each step must work before moving to the next. Do not skip ahead.

### Phase 1 — Foundation (no LLM needed)

```
Step 1: config.py
        Define all settings. DB_BACKEND = "sqlite" for local.
        Rollup table specs with single-source-of-truth names.

Step 2: db/dialect.py + db/sqlite_backend.py
        Implement the SQLite dialect. Test: can execute raw SQL, handles
        date functions, handles the array-as-junction-table pattern.

Step 3: synthetic/generate.py
        Generate local.db. Verify: row counts, distributions, junction table
        populated, all 4 datamarts built with correct aggregations.

Step 4: schema/cache.py
        Introspect the SQLite database. Write schema_cache.json.
        Verify: all tables and columns listed, types correct.
```

### Phase 2 — Rule-Based Agents (no LLM needed)

```
Step 5: agents/chart_type.py
        Feed it hand-built DataFrames of each shape. Verify each rule fires.

Step 6: agents/ui_designer.py
        Feed it mixed chart lists. Verify 12-column layout math.
```

### Phase 3 — LLM-Dependent Agents (needs model endpoint)

For local testing, you have two options:
- Point at a local LLM (if you have one running).
- Mock the LLM responses to test the wiring. Use a simple mock that returns canned JSON in the expected format.

```
Step 7: agents/planner.py
        Test with vague + specific + mixed prompts. Verify sub-question
        decomposition, pinned chart handling, clarification triggering.

Step 8: training/ + agents/data_wrangler.py
        Train Vanna locally. Test: "trend of success rate over 30 days"
        should generate SQL targeting daily_kpi_summary, not bxb_dw.

Step 9: agents/diagnose.py
        Feed it a broken SQL + error message. Verify one-sentence diagnosis.

Step 10: agents/insights.py
         Feed it chart data. Verify 2-4 observations with real numbers.
```

### Phase 4 — Orchestration

```
Step 11: agents/orchestrator.py
         Wire all agents into LangGraph. Test happy path end-to-end.
         (Skip Superset calls — mock them or print the chart configs.)

Step 12: Clarification pause/resume
         Send ambiguous prompt. Verify pause. Resume with thread_id.

Step 13: Retry/skip branch
         Force a SQL error. Verify diagnose → retry → eventual skip.
```

### Phase 5 — External Integrations

```
Step 14: agents/dashboard_codegen.py
         Connect to Superset (if available locally). Create one chart.

Step 15: agents/scheduler.py
         Test all three job types: schema refresh, rollup maintenance,
         recurring dashboard.

Step 16: api/server.py
         FastAPI endpoints. Full HTTP round-trip test.
```

### Phase 6 — Production Prep

```
Step 17: db/bigquery_backend.py
         Implement BigQueryDialect. CANNOT test locally — just write it
         correctly using the schema info from Section 2 above.
         Uses google-cloud-bigquery with ADC auth:
             from google.cloud import bigquery
             client = bigquery.Client()  # ADC auto-discovers credentials

Step 18: training/train_bigquery.py
         Write it. CANNOT run locally — will be run on Samsung VM.

Step 19: Audit all hardcoded strings
         Grep for any raw table names, column names, project IDs in
         agent code. ALL must come from config.py.
```

